// @run
// @log 1
// @log 42
// Forward reference between top-level functions: `a` calls `b`, which is
// declared LATER in the file. VL's parser resolves names in a single
// top-to-bottom pass, so before the forward-reference pre-pass this failed with
// `Syntax error: undeclared b`. The pre-pass now hoists every top-level
// function *signature* into the module scope before any body is type-checked, so
// a call resolves regardless of declaration order. Codegen references wasm
// functions by index, which are inherently forward-referenceable, so lowering
// already tolerated this once typecheck did.
function a(): i32 { return b() }
function b(): i32 { return 1 }
print(a())

// A longer forward chain: each function calls the next, all declared after.
function first(): i32 { return second() }
function second(): i32 { return third() }
function third(): i32 { return 42 }
print(first())
